ZH: 磁场是空间中的一种物理现象。
EN: The magnetic field is a physical phenomenon in space.

ZH: 磁场是由电荷运动产生的。
EN: The magnetic field is generated by the movement of electric charges.

ZH: 地球上有一个很强的磁场，用于保护我们免受太阳辐射的危害。
EN: The Earth has a strong magnetic field that protects us from solar radiation.

ZH: 我们可以通过磁场感应定位地理位置。
EN: We can use magnetic field induction to locate geographic positions.

ZH: 磁场在许多工业和科学应用中起到重要作用。
EN: Magnetic fields play an important role in many industrial and scientific applications.

ZH: 磁场也可以用于磁共振成像。
EN: Magnetic fields can also be used for magnetic resonance imaging.

ZH: 磁场可以通过磁铁被引导。
EN: Magnetic fields can be guided by magnets.

ZH: 磁场对金属材料具有特殊的影响。
EN: Magnetic fields have a special influence on metallic materials.

ZH: 磁场的方向可以通过右手定则确定。
EN: The direction of a magnetic field can be determined by the right-hand rule.

ZH: 磁场的大小和强度取决于电流的大小。
EN: The size and strength of a magnetic field depend on the size of the current.

ZH: 磁场可以在真空中传播。
EN: Magnetic fields can propagate in a vacuum.

ZH: 磁场对生物体也有一定的影响。
EN: Magnetic fields also have an impact on living organisms.

ZH: 研究人员正在研究磁场在医学领域的应用。
EN: Researchers are studying the application of magnetic fields in the medical field.

ZH: 磁场可以通过线圈来产生。
EN: Magnetic fields can be generated by coils.

ZH: 磁场对电子具有一定的影响。
EN: Magnetic fields have a certain influence on electrons.

ZH: 磁场的作用机制还有待进一步研究。
EN: The mechanism of action of magnetic fields still needs further research.

ZH: 磁场在地磁导航中具有重要意义。
EN: The magnetic field plays an important role in geomagnetic navigation.

ZH: 磁场能够产生力，导致磁力线上的物体受力。
EN: The magnetic field can generate force, causing objects on magnetic field lines to experience force.

ZH: 磁场可以通过磁铁的南北极来描述。
EN: Magnetic fields can be described by the north and south poles of a magnet.

ZH: 磁场可以通过磁感应强度来衡量。
EN: Magnetic fields can be measured by magnetic induction strength.
